body: "Nightly run 29676618564 (2026-07-19): windows/Node24 leg red on TWO specs — the known pm-hvt3 extension-copy-safety spec plus a NEW failure in tests/unit/packages/vcs-extension.spec.ts (\"executes every source command and guarded failure boundary through the host SDK context\"). macOS leg carries only the hvt3 spec.\n\nRoot cause: line 402 (introduced by PR#605, workspace-transactions lane) asserts `defaultPathStore.path` contains the POSIX literal \"relationships/events.jsonl\"; on Windows the relationship event store default path renders with backslashes, so `toContain` fails. Product behavior is correct (native separators); this is a spec-side portability defect — same class as closed pm-u5zr (POSIX endsWith), pm-lt6n, pm-s5pe, pm-i84i.\n\nFix: assert via `path.join(\"relationships\", \"events.jsonl\")` (spec already imports node:path). Windows leg goes fully green only together with pm-hvt3."
